        "forum_post":"\u00a0 \u00a0 Hi Bunyapine,\u00a0 \u00a0 Yes, changing formula can put you into waves, I found out about that the hard way last year when I knew nothing about crossovers. I changed from water titrating my original tablet to water titrating a compounded capsule, and ended up in a three month wave or so. I decided to go back to the the tablet, because it\u2019s more accurate, and did a crossover this time. It went well.\u00a0 \u00a0 This is the formula for the crossover, as ChessieCat mentioned above.\u00a0 \u00a0 3\/4 of the old formula. \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a01\/4 of the liquid.\u00a0 \u00a0 1\/2 of the old formula. \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a01\/2 of the liquid.\u00a0 \u00a0 1\/4 of the old formula. \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 3\/4 of the liquid.\u00a0 \u00a0 You do every stage for 3 days to a week, though I did each stage for more than a week to be safe.\u00a0 \u00a0 I just saw in your signature that you jumped from\u00a0125mg to 25mg in January, and then from 25mg to 12.5mg in February. Is that correct?\u00a0They are huge drops if that\u2019s the case.\u00a0I wouldn\u2019t be doing any tapering as yet until you are stable. I would wait a number of months before I changed anything.\u00a0One should never taper by more than 10% a month, I\u2019m\u00a0tapering just over 3% at the moment.\u00a0 \u00a0 Whatever you do DO NOT jump off at 12.5mg like the doctor suggested, and DO NOT do two changes at the same time.\u00a0 \u00a0 If your doctor doesn\u2019t cooperate with you just try another doctor. Any doctor can give you a script, it doesn\u2019t have to be a psychiatrist. \u00a0 Please be careful, and hold for a while longer. You\u2019ve tapered too quickly, and your brain needs time to stabilise before you change anything else.\u00a0 \u00a0 Sending hugs\ud83e\udd17 \u00a0",
