        "forum_post":"Fellow Survivors, \u00a0 A few things to report\u2026. \u00a0 Thankfully, I heeded the advice of some withdrawal veterans on here and held at 3 mg, re-read the post on the KISS principles and waited. \u00a0I have stabilized, sleeping and feeling great, sometimes a little euphoric. \u00a0So well in fact, that I sampled a little caffeine\u00a0the other morning to see what would happen. \u00a0I switched to decaf 8 months ago but I thought I'd slightly increase the caffeine level and observe. \u00a0NO REACTION! I thought any second the cortisol\/ adrenalin would flood my system but it didn't happen, felt amazing! \u00a0I have drastically changed my diet\u2026low carb, no sugar, no processed crap, no alcohol and high fats including Coconut oil, MCT oil, grass-fed butter coupled with a light exercise regime and I think the CNS loves this style and rewarded me with a little caffeine tolerance\u00a0  . \u00a0When things were s&*% a few weeks back, I was really strict with the above and added heart math and other meditation techniques everyday and things evened out. \u00a0The drops had caught up with me and decided to give me a swift smack upside the head. \u00a0\"Ok I get it, I will slow down a little!\" \u00a0 \u00a0 Secondly, for the benzo sufferers\u2026. \u00a0 Last week marks 1 year out from Klonipin and I can honestly say, based on where I was a year prior, I have healed exponentially. \u00a0I chose to use Remeron to ease this withdrawal and am paying the price for it now, but, I would say, 90% of the horrible symptoms are gone. \u00a0I am fully functional, returned to work a long time ago and doing pretty darn well considering. \u00a0Yes, I have setbacks and have grown accustomed to those annoying floaters but compared to tolerance withdrawal (6 months) and acute withdrawal, not even close. \u00a0I had all of the horrid symptoms and most of them resolved\u2026gone!! \u00a0 \u00a0 So keep pushing, keep fighting\u2026try to find the stability that your CNS and brain require and go slow. \u00a0If your sleep deprived, withdrawal rattled brain wants to change things rapidly to fix your situation\u2026..read the KISS post on this site, take a breath and wait it out\u2026.if that means a longer hold or slowing taper down..try to do it. \u00a0I laugh when I look at my previous posts where I was desperate\u2026thankfully the support was here to help show me the way. \u00a0I am eternally grateful for that. \u00a0Everyone of us on this site who continue to fight have my deepest respect, you are heroes, don't forget that. \u00a0 Take care \u00a0 BB",
